The first couple of months for a new government are always crucial as this is the time when it lays down its broad framework of policies and their thrust areas. A government that fails to make the right impact in this period often regrets its lack of focus or urgency later during its tenure. The Narendra was sworn in on May 26. Two months will be over by the end of this week. This, therefore, is a good time to assess what the key signals on governance the new regime has sent out in the last few weeks.
